  "optimization_hints": [
    "Q1: Full scan lineitem (60M rows) with single date predicate; hash aggregation over 4 groups. Use zone-map index on l_shipdate; operator fusion for scan+filter+agg.",
    "Q3: Three-way hash join (customer→orders→lineitem) with selective filters; push c_mktsegment and date filters early. LIMIT 10 enables top-K. Partial aggregation reduces intermediate size.",
    "Q6: Highly selective range filters on date/discount/quantity reduce data to <1% before aggregation. Branch-free SIMD filtering on numeric predicates. Single COUNT aggregate.",
    "Q9: Complex 6-way join; push LIKE filter on part early (reduces to 4.8%); use join ordering to minimize intermediates (part→partsupp→supplier→nation reduces breadth). Sorted aggregation if nation dimension is small.",
    "Q18: Subquery is materialization point - filter lineitem GROUP BY l_orderkey with HAVING before main join. Hash semi-join for IN subquery optimization. LIMIT 100 enables partial sort."
  ],
  "critical_path": "Lineitem table dominates cost (60M rows). Q1/Q6/Q9 scan lineitem; Q3/Q18 join orders+lineitem. Execution order: apply all predicates early, use hash joins on larger tables, enable parallelism on scans/joins/aggs.",
  "summary": "TPC-H 10GB fact table (lineitem 60M rows) with star schema (5 small dimensions). Dominant pattern: full-scan aggregations (Q1) and selective range scans with multi-way joins (Q3, Q9, Q18). Q1 and Q6 are CPU-bound aggregations (vectorization + SIMD payoff). Q3/Q9/Q18 are join-bound; optimize join order and filter pushdown. All queries benefit from parallelism (32 cores available). Critical optimization lever: early filter pushdown and partial aggregation to reduce intermediate cardinalities by 10-100x."
}
